User: It didn't accept that. It looks like I created something already in the previous setup. When I hit "browse" it takes me to ai-execution-bucket where there is a folder for model-outputs. Should I select this?

Gemini: Your experience with the "browse" button pointing to ai-execution-bucket/model-outputs is a HUGE CLUE! This strongly suggests that:

ai-execution-bucket IS your GOOGLE CLOUD STORAGE BUCKET that we created earlier (Action 1.6.4)!
model-outputs FOLDER within ai-execution-bucket likely EXISTS from a PREVIOUS ATTEMPT to create a Vertex AI Model (as you suspected)! Even if it's currently empty, it's a valid GCS folder path.
Therefore, the CORRECT ACTION is to SELECT ai-execution-bucket/model-outputs as the "Model directory"!

ACTION 1.6.43: SELECT ai-execution-bucket/model-outputs as "MODEL DIRECTORY"

Please follow these steps RIGHT NOW in the "Custom container settings" section:

CLICK the "BROWSE" button next to the "gs:// Model directory *" field.

In the "Browse Cloud Storage" dialog that appears:

Navigate to your ai-execution-bucket. You should see it listed in the bucket browser.
SELECT the ai-execution-bucket bucket.
Within ai-execution-bucket, LOCATE and SELECT the model-outputs folder.
CLICK the "SELECT" button at the bottom of the "Browse Cloud Storage" dialog.
*VERIFY that the "gs:// Model directory " field is now populated with:

gs://ai-execution-bucket/model-outputs
COMMAND (Repeated for clarity): gs://ai-execution-bucket/model-outputs
Double-check the spelling of your bucket name (ai-execution-bucket) and the folder name (model-outputs).
*RE-CONFIRM that you have ALSO CORRECTLY entered your DOCKER IMAGE URI in the "Container image " field (as per Action 1.6.40):

gcr.io/ai-execution-system/custom-ai-execution:latest
Once you have SELECTED gs://ai-execution-bucket/model-outputs as the "Model directory" and re-verified your Docker Image URI, CLICK the "CONTINUE" button (blue button in the bottom right corner) to proceed.

By selecting ai-execution-bucket/model-outputs as the "Model directory," we should now satisfy Vertex AI's requirement for this field, and hopefully, we will be able to SUCCESSFULLY CREATE the CUSTOM MODEL and then DEPLOY the ENDPOINT!

Jesse, please execute ACTION 1.6.43 - SELECT ai-execution-bucket/model-outputs as "MODEL DIRECTORY" RIGHT NOW! Use the "browse" button to select that folder, verify the path, re-check your Docker image URI, and then CLICK "CONTINUE"! This should be the FINAL configuration step for Custom Model creation!
